{
  "texts": [
    "Machine translation, also known as automatic translation, is the process of converting one natural language (source language) into another natural language (target language) using a computer.",
    "It is a branch of computational linguistics, one of the ultimate goals of artificial intelligence, and has important scientific research value.",
    "Machine translation systems can be divided into two categories: rulebased and corpus-based.",
    "The former comprises a dictionary and a rule base, which collectively constitute the knowledge source.",
    "In contrast, the latter comprises a corpus that has been divided and labeled, and which does not require a dictionary or rules."
  ]
}